```puml
@startuml Gestion_Absences_Sequence_Auth
title Flux d'Authentification - Diagramme de Séquence

actor Client
participant "API Gateway" as Gateway
participant "AuthController" as Controller
participant "AuthService" as Service
participant "UserRepository" as Repo
participant "Database" as DB

Client ->> Gateway: POST /api/auth/login
activate Gateway

Gateway ->> Controller: LoginDto(email, password)
activate Controller

Controller ->> Service: Login(LoginDto)
activate Service

Service ->> Repo: GetUserByEmail(email)
activate Repo

Repo ->> DB: SELECT * FROM Users WHERE Email = @email
activate DB
DB -->> Repo: User record
deactivate DB

Repo -->> Service: User
deactivate Repo

Service ->> Service: VerifyPassword(password, hash)
Note over Service: BCrypt.Verify()

Service ->> Service: GenerateAccessToken(User)
Note over Service: JWT Token (15 min)

Service ->> Service: GenerateRefreshToken(User)
Note over Service: JWT Token (7 days)

Service ->> Repo: SaveRefreshToken(token)
activate Repo
Repo ->> DB: INSERT INTO RefreshTokens
activate DB
DB -->> Repo: OK
deactivate DB
Repo -->> Service: OK
deactivate Repo

Service -->> Controller: TokenResponse(accessToken, refreshToken)
deactivate Service

Controller -->> Gateway: 200 OK + Tokens
deactivate Controller

Gateway -->> Client: JSON Response
deactivate Gateway

Note over Client: Client stocke tokens localement

Client ->> Gateway: GET /api/users/profile
Note over Gateway: Header: Authorization: Bearer {accessToken}
activate Gateway

Gateway ->> Gateway: ValidateToken(accessToken)
Note over Gateway: Vérifier signature & expiration

alt Token valide
    Gateway ->> Controller: Request authentifié
    Controller -->> Client: 200 OK + User Data
else Token expiré
    Gateway -->> Client: 401 Unauthorized
    Client ->> Gateway: POST /api/auth/refresh-token
    Gateway ->> Service: Refresh(refreshToken)
    Service -->> Client: Nouveau accessToken
end

deactivate Gateway

@enduml
```
